This is an independent, clean-room implementation. It was written from a
behavioural specification (see docs/SPEC.md) describing the desired
functionality of a macOS menu-bar account switcher for AI coding CLIs. No
third-party source code was copied, decompiled, or translated into this
project.

The functionality (switching between multiple CLI accounts, OAuth token
refresh, macOS Keychain access, a SwiftUI menu-bar UI) is implemented using
standard, publicly documented APIs and idioms. Module structure, naming, UI
strings, configuration format and the auto-switch policy are this project's own
design.

Built with Swift and Apple's SwiftUI / AppKit frameworks. No third-party
runtime dependencies.
